 from his maternal grandmother Lucilla Kirtland Gridley — the same surname his uncle John Kirtland Gridley had inherited as a middle name a generation earlier. The Kirtland surname passed through three Gridley-Fowler generations as a middle name without anyone in the family carrying it as a last name."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Melissa Craven Fowler — Fowler family genealogist","url":"https://www.melissacravenfowler.com/"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"edward-fowler-1832"},"X02661":{"id":"X02661","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Eunice","middle_name":"Tower","last_name":"Fowler","maiden_name":"Eddy","married_names":["Fowler"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Eunice Tower Eddy Fowler"},"birth":{"year":1841,"city":"Oakland County","state":"Michigan","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1928,"city":"St. Louis","state":"Michigan","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM208","plot_notes":"Oak Grove Cemetery, St. Louis Gratiot County MI. Per Abel Fowler genealogy."},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_name":"James Eddy","mother_name":"Mary S. Tower Eddy","father_research_notes":"James Eddy. Per Descendants of Abel Fowler PDF.","mother_research_notes":"Mary S. Tower Eddy. Per Descendants of Abel Fowler PDF."},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H03720","date_year":1861,"date_month":6,"date_day":30,"location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1898,"children_ids":["HD3509","HD3510","HD3511","HD3512"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Melissa Craven Fowler — Fowler family genealogist","url":"https://www.melissacravenfowler.com/"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"eunice-eddy-1841"},"X02653":{"id":"X02653","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Anson","last_name":"Fowler","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Anson Fowler"},"birth":{"year":1809,"month":2,"day":15,"city":"Fairfield","county":"Herkimer","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1855,"month":3,"day":15,"city":"Wheatland Township","county":"Hillsdale","state":"Michigan","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM207","plot_notes":"Churches Corners Cemetery, Wheatland Township Hillsdale County MI."},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_name":"Abel Fowler","mother_name":"Mary Eddy Fowler","father_research_notes":"Abel Fowler of Churchville NY. Per EH 1909 entry 2242 and the published Fowler genealogy 'Descendants of Abel Fowler.'","mother_research_notes":"Mary Eddy Fowler. Per EH 1909 entry 2242."},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H02242","date_year":1831,"date_month":2,"date_day":12,"location_city":"Ogden","location_county":"Monroe","location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1855,"children_ids":["H03720","H03721","H03722","H03723","H03724"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["new_york_migration","michigan_migration"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"character","header":"Origin of the name Anson remains uncertain","body":"Anson was born in Fairfield Herkimer County NY in 1809 to Abel and Mary Eddy Fowler — but the Fowler line shows no documented earlier Anson. Genealogists have suggested the name may trace to Mary's possible Eddy or Ross matrilineal kin: a William Anson Eddy and an Anson Ross were both born around 1809, and three Ross sisters had married three Eddy brothers in that family network. Whether the name came from those collateral relatives or from a popular contemporary figure named Anson is unresolved."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Frontier child became Michigan land-patent pioneer","body":"Anson was about seven when his parents moved the family west from Herkimer County NY to Genesee County NY around 1816. After marrying Harriet Louisa Gridley in Ogden NY in 1831, the couple bought land in Wheatland Township Hillsdale County Michigan from a federal land office in 1835 — second-wave New England migration into the Old Northwest. Three of their five surviving children were born in Wheatland on that patent."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Melissa Craven Fowler — Fowler family genealogist","url":"https://www.melissacravenfowler.com/"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"anson-fowler-1809"},"H02242":{"id":"H02242","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Harriet","middle_name":"Louisa","last_name":"Fowler","maiden_name":"Gridley","married_names":["Fowler"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Harriet Louisa Gridley Fowler"},"birth":{"year":1810,"month":5,"day":12,"city":"Pompey","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1898,"month":11,"day":7,"city":"Wheatland Township","county":"Hillsdale","state":"Michigan","country":"United States"},"residence":{"city":"Wheatland Township","county":"Hillsdale","state":"Michigan","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM207","plot_notes":"Churches Corners Cemetery, Wheatland Township Hillsdale County MI. Per Abel Fowler genealogy."},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":8,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"H01093","mother_id":"X02649"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X02653","date_year":1831,"date_month":2,"date_day":12,"location_city":"Ogden","location_county":"Monroe","location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1855,"children_ids":["H03720","H03721","H03722","H03723","H03724"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["michigan_migration","new_york_migration"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Pioneer Hooker line into Michigan","body":"Harriet Louisa Gridley and Anson Fowler married at Ogden NY in 1831 and later migrated to Wheatland Township in Hillsdale County Michigan — among the first Hooker-descended families to settle west of New York. Four of their five children were born in Michigan; Anson is buried at Churches Corners Cemetery there."},{"number":2,"category":"character","header":"Charter member of frontier Free-Will Baptist Church","body":"Harriet was an early member of the First Free-Will Baptist Church of Wheatland Michigan, organized February 19, 1838 in Eli Eastman's home shortly after the Fowlers arrived. The church gathered at Church's Corners just a few miles from her farm; local accounts noted that before the congregation organized, 'there was more rifle-shooting done on Sunday than any other day.'"},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Widowed at forty-five, managed her own land deals","body":"When Anson died in 1855 Harriet was forty-five, with five surviving children. Hillsdale County records show her buying and selling acreage within a few miles of the original 1835 patent for the next two decades — alone or jointly with relatives. She remained financially comfortable through the 1870 and 1880 censuses, outlived Anson by forty-three years, and died in Wheatland Township in 1898."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Descendants of Abel Fowler (Wix-hosted PDF)","url":"https://docs.wixstatic.com/ugd/c44016_98436f8b114248ff82fee17977f0097b.pdf"},{"label":"Melissa Craven Fowler — Fowler family genealogist","url":"https://www.melissacravenfowler.com/"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"harriet-fowler-1810"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM208","name":"Oak Grove Cemetery","city":"St. Louis","county":"Gratiot","state":"Michigan","country":"United States","visitable":true,"hooker_connections":["H03720","HD3511","X02661","I01723"],"notes":"Oak Grove Cemetery, St. Louis, Gratiot County, Michigan. Burial place of Edward Kirtland Fowler (H03720, 1832-1898) and his wife Eunice Tower Eddy Fowler (X02661, 1841-1928). Distinct from Oak Grove cemeteries elsewhere. Per Descendants of Abel Fowler PDF."},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}